OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776795065
OL,3,CWhy does the King think we live in
OL,4,C'deeply troubling' times?
OL,6,FWhat did King Charles mean when he
OL,7,Fsaid his mother would have been
OL,8,Ftroubled "deeply" by so many events
OL,9,Faround the world today?
OL,26,@pD@JOUpD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31002
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776795065
OL,3,CWhy does the King think we live in
OL,4,C'deeply troubling' times?
OL,6,FThere are many candidates which would
OL,7,Fqualify as "troubling" right now: wars
OL,8,Fin Iran, suffering in Gaza, a Pope
OL,9,Funder attack from a president, people
OL,10,Fbeing targeted because of their faith
OL,11,For their ethnicity, a Russian war of
OL,12,Faggression in Europe, a planet on
OL,13,Fwhich the climate and biodiversity is
OL,14,Fat a tipping point, energy prices
OL,15,Frocketing and, at home, the King's
OL,16,Fprime minister seemingly stepping from
OL,17,Fone crisis straight into another.
OL,19,FIt's not a short list.
OL,26,@oD@LOUoD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31003
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776795065
OL,3,CWhy does the King think we live in
OL,4,C'deeply troubling' times?
OL,6,FAnd the King is about to spend four
OL,7,Fdays in the United States with a
OL,8,Fleader who has instigated at least
OL,9,Fsome of those troubles.
OL,11,FBuckingham Palace won't expand on
OL,12,Fexactly what King Charles meant by his
OL,13,Fphrase, but it is recognition that
OL,14,Fmany of us are finding these times
OL,15,F"deeply troubling" and he clearly
OL,16,Fthought it worth it a mention in a
OL,17,Frare video address that was about
OL,18,Fmarking 100 years since the birth of
OL,19,FQueen Elizabeth II.
OL,26,@wD@AOUwD@RO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31004
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776795065
OL,3,CWhy does the King think we live in
OL,4,C'deeply troubling' times?
OL,6,FHer reign was one which witnessed, as
OL,7,Fthe King wrote "remarkable change" and
OL,8,Fyet the late Queen was a constant and
OL,9,Fsteadfast symbol of reassurance for so
OL,10,Fmany.
OL,12,FGiven how admired and respected she
OL,13,Fwas, and given the length of her
OL,14,Freign, it's remarkable that the
OL,15,Ftransition from Elizabeth to her
OL,16,Feldest son, Charles, happened so
OL,17,Fsmoothly.
OL,26,@oD@POUoD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31005
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776795065
OL,3,CWhy does the King think we live in
OL,4,C'deeply troubling' times?
OL,6,FRecent opinion polls might have Prince
OL,7,FWilliam and Kate as the most popular
OL,8,Froyals, but there has been barely a
OL,9,Fflicker in the levels of support for
OL,10,Fthe institution of monarchy which King
OL,11,FCharles now leads.
OL,13,FA YouGov tracker found support for
OL,14,Fmonarchy at 64% although, as usual,
OL,15,Fthere is much less enthusiasm for the
OL,16,FRoyal Family among younger Britons.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31006
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776795065
OL,3,CWhy does the King think we live in
OL,4,C'deeply troubling' times?
OL,6,FIt's all the more remarkable when you
OL,7,Fconsider that this King has had to
OL,8,Fdeal with the scandal engulfing his
OL,9,Fyounger brother, Andrew Mountbatten-
OL,10,FWindsor.
OL,12,FBy removing Andrew's prince title, his
OL,13,Fdukedom and his rental agreement with
OL,14,Fthe taxpayer-linked Crown Estate, the
OL,15,FKing was attempting to show support
OL,16,Ffor the survivors of Jeffrey Epstein's
OL,17,Fabuse and limit the damage the former
OL,18,Fprince was doing to the national and
OL,19,Fglobal reputation of the British Royal
OL,20,FFamily.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31007
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776795065
OL,3,CWhy does the King think we live in
OL,4,C'deeply troubling' times?
OL,6,FAnd, as many have noted, those options
OL,7,Fwere open to Queen Elizabeth after
OL,8,FAndrew's Newsnight catastrophe, but
OL,9,Fshe chose not to take them.
OL,11,FMr Mountbatten-Windsor has
OL,12,Fconsistently denied any wrongdoing.
OL,14,FAndrew always was a bit of a "blind
OL,15,Fspot" for the late Queen, according to
OL,16,Fthose who worked for her for so many
OL,17,Fyears.
OL,26,@vD@^OUwD@EO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31008
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776795065
OL,3,CWhy does the King think we live in
OL,4,C'deeply troubling' times?
OL,6,FBut on what would have been her 100th
OL,7,Fbirthday, we will get the largest
OL,8,Fgathering of working royals that we've
OL,9,Fseen for some time.
OL,11,FThe King and Queen, his heir Prince
OL,12,FWilliam and the Princess of Wales,
OL,13,FPrincess Anne, Prince Edward and the
OL,14,Flate Queen's cousins, the Gloucesters
OL,15,Fand Kents.
OL,17,FNo Prince Harry at Buckingham Palace,
OL,18,Fof course, who is just back from his
OL,19,Fpart-money-making, part-charity tour
OL,20,Fto Australia with his wife Meghan.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31009
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776795065
OL,3,CWhy does the King think we live in
OL,4,C'deeply troubling' times?
OL,6,FAs one of our colleagues in Australia
OL,7,Ftold our Talking Royals podcast last
OL,8,Fweek, some people down under thought
OL,9,Fthe Duke and Duchess of Sussex were
OL,10,Ftreating the country like a bit of "an
OL,11,FATM".
OL,13,FThe late Queen was very fond of her
OL,14,Fgrandson, but he and Meghan did create
OL,15,Fsome obvious difficulties for her in
OL,16,Fthe last years of her life.
OL,18,FWe should never forget at times like
OL,19,Fthese that this King still has cancer
OL,20,Fand still requires treatment for it.
OL,26,@rD@dOUsD@DO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31010
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776795065
OL,3,CWhy does the King think we live in
OL,4,C'deeply troubling' times?
OL,6,FSo it says something about his own
OL,7,Fcommitment to service that he ploughs
OL,8,Fon at full-speed in the way that he
OL,9,Fdoes.
OL,11,FCharles' State Visit to the US next
OL,12,Fweek will require him to deploy all
OL,13,Fthe diplomatic skills he's acquired
OL,14,Fduring his long years as heir and more
OL,15,Frecent years as King.
OL,17,FHe spoke today of his mother's belief
OL,18,Fthat "goodness will always prevail" so
OL,19,Fperhaps she'll be watching over events
OL,20,Fin the White House next week with a
OL,21,Flittle intrigue.
OL,26,@zD@FOUzD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/12
